The paper deals with the problem of secure message transmission, which is a central topic in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The authors focus on the communication complexity of the protocol, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The protocol also involves the use of multiple channels, which is a common theme in network security (cs.NI). Finally, the authors mention the adaptation of their protocol to a network coding context, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS).
